## Summary

| Severity | Count | Pattern |
|---|---|---|
| 🔴 Critical | 6 | Zero assertions — method called, nothing verified |
| 🟠 High | 4 | `IsNotNull` on non-nullable return types |
| 🟡 Medium | 6+ | Missing negative/edge-case paths entirely |

**Root cause:** Every test follows the same template — call the method, optionally `Assert.IsNotNull`, done. This is a classic **"coverage theater"** suite: it touches every line to hit the coverage gate but verifies no business logic. The fix is to assert on **values and state changes**, not just non-nullity.
